---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.tsx'
import '../index.css'
---

<Layout title="About - PhyloGuessr">
  <div class="game">
    <Header client:load />
    <div class="about-page">
      <h2>About PhyloGuessr</h2>

      <h3>How it works</h3>
      <p>Pick which two of three organisms are most closely related — the pair sharing the most recent common ancestor.</p>

      <h3>Data sources</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Phylogeny from the <a href="https://tree.opentreeoflife.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Tree of Life</a></li>
        <li>Species names from <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/taxonomy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NCBI Taxonomy</a></li>
        <li>Images from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Wikipedia</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Why Open Tree of Life?</h3>
      <p>NCBI Taxonomy is a classification, not a phylogeny — it often can't resolve which two of three species are closest (a "polytomy"). The Open Tree synthesizes published phylogenetic studies for better resolution. For example, NCBI leaves primates, colugos, and rodents unresolved within Euarchontoglires, while the Open Tree correctly groups colugos with primates.</p>

      <h3>Contribute</h3>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/cmdcolin/phyloguessr" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> · <a href="https://github.com/cmdcolin/phyloguessr/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Report bugs or suggest trios</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
